      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "\nAs I understand it, Bob Dewar, Ron Hochsprung and others in the Computer Center decided to make a more friendly language than the miserable IBM FORTRAN for students to learn to program with. Thus was born IITRAN - a sort of relaxed FORTRAN, interpreted, not compiled, with simplified I/O facilities and a very tolerant syntax.",
      "id": "5b89dcd5850b6538a44df768516fb58b"
    },
